  1. Keyword

    1. strictftp: modifier of method. The method will use strict 64-bit floating point to do floating number operation.
      Intel processor has a 80-bit floating point register. This 80-bit register can increase the precision of result.
      However, for the processor that does not have the 80-bit register, they will generate different result.
      Therefore, in order to yield reproducible results, you can use the "strictftp" to kill this benefit. 
                  public staticftp float add(float x, float y){

            }
